        <briefdescription>
<para>Initialize the Redundancy Manager. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Clears all faults, sets system health to SYSTEM_HEALTH_OK, and subscribes to:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Fault events from all services (e.g., BATTERY_EVENT_FAULT_DETECTED)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Query request events from applications</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Recovery events from services</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Publishes initial REDUNDANCY_EVENT_HEALTH_RECOVERED event after init.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="inout">manager</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The redundancy manager to initialize. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
